This package contains all Drizzle ORM schemas, migrations, and DB helpers for OpenNG.

## Schema Organization
- packages/db/src/public/ — production table schemas (PostgreSQL "public" schema)
- packages/db/src/staging/ — staging table schemas (staging schema, includes audit columns)
- packages/db/src/ref/ — reference/lookup table schemas (ref schema, read-only after seed)
- packages/db/src/analytics/ — usage analytics schemas (analytics schema)
- packages/db/src/procedures/ — SQL stored procedure files (the ONLY place raw SQL is allowed)

## Standard Columns
Every production table MUST include these columns:
- id: BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY
- source_url: TEXT NOT NULL
- source_date: DATE NOT NULL
- created_at: TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
- updated_at: TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT NOW()
- is_active: BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT TRUE

Every staging table MUST additionally include:
- is_valid: BOOLEAN DEFAULT NULL
- validation_note: TEXT DEFAULT NULL
- flagged: BOOLEAN DEFAULT NULL
- flagged_reason: TEXT DEFAULT NULL
- migrated_at: TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NULL
- import_batch_id: UUID NOT NULL

## Naming
- Tables: snake_case, plural (fuel_prices, postal_codes, holidays)
- Columns: snake_case (pms_price, state_id, source_url)
- Foreign keys: {referenced_table_singular}_id (state_id, lga_id, commodity_id)
- Indexes: idx_{table}_{columns} (idx_fuel_prices_state_period)
- Stored procedures: {schema}.{verb}_{resource} (staging.validate_fuel)

## Security
- Never store secrets in plaintext — hash API keys, tokens, passwords with SHA-256
- All queries use Drizzle's parameterized query builder — never concatenate user input into SQL
- The API reads exclusively from public and ref — it never writes to public directly
- All writes to public go through migration stored procedures only

## Query Patterns
- Use Drizzle's query builder for all application queries
- Raw SQL is ONLY allowed in stored procedure files under src/procedures/
- Always use parameterized inputs in stored procedures
- Never return unbounded result sets — all list queries must use LIMIT and OFFSET
